post_text: Thank you so much for joining my free online art lessons. I started this as a way for my small business to connect with my art students and our community while families are homebound. Now I have met so many wonderful art students around the globe! I am so happy to offer these at no charge, as art can be the best way to work through the most difficult times. I did have requests to make a small thank you donation to my small business during this time. It is not necessary, as we are all in the same boat, but for those that asked or felt led, here is the link:

post_text: Join me live today at 1pm Central Time...Have paper and pencils ready, dark-colored markers (black if you have them), and a bit of very strong coffee. Why coffee? It is to paint with to show you how to create with items around the house for those who don't have lots of art supplies at the ready. You may also use watercolors if you prefer. If you can't MAKE it then, I post the videos afterwards to Facebook here @makepaducah and YouTube @Kijsa Housman.

Class List March 23-27
Happy Saturday fabulous Artists!! Class will be back in session this Monday, March 23 at 1pm Central time!
Here's our list of learning for next week, as well as supplies. I am trying to work my lessons around basic items you might already have handy as we all stay close to home these days. If you don't have them all on hand, join in anyway and learn along with us:

Monday: Perspective with Leonardo
(papers, pencils, ruler or straight edge)

Tuesday: Good Hare Day
(pencils, heavyweight or watercolor paper, cold very strong coffee or tea, black markers or pens)

Wednesday: The Great Wave
Heavyweight paper or watercolor paper, pencils, watercolors, brushes, varying 1"-3" round shapes to trace, dark-color markers

Thursday: Contour Lines
(pencils, paper, Paper plate or similarly sized cardboard, fruit or vegetables to draw, not to eat üôÇ

Friday: Fab Flat Face Sculpture
(pencils, paper, homemade clay (we will make during class) using a big bowl, 2c flour, 1c salt, 2TB oil and 1c water)

-White school glue (1cup)
-Food coloring or liquid watercolor
-Large bowl you don‚Äôt mind getting messy, plus 3-5 smaller disposable bowls
-Quart zip-top sandwich bags
-Heavy weight paper or board (cardboard, paper plate, watercolor paper)

-Brushes

post_text:
Please share:

Due to school closures, I will be offering free art lessons on our Facebook page each weekday until our kiddos return to school. These will be family oriented for a range of ages and utilize supplies typically found in your home.

Creativity can ease stress, expedite learning & allow us to see circumstances in different ways. Since we will all be home gathered together over the next few weeks unexpectedly, it is the perfect time to discover and grow new talent! We will be offering take home kits from the studio for additional lessons beginning next Wednesday.
I always pull from my classical training as a BFA studio art major and 25 years as a professional artist, but also love to introduce process learning- In other words- I like to show you how to do it AND get messy!

Join us at 1pm CT this Monday for our first lesson!
Hint: For Monday, gather plain paper, a baking sheet, cooking spray/oil and pencils...we will be drawing faces!

A time for Mom (or caregiver) to share with their little one. Recommended for ages 18mos-4 years, this class introduces art concepts using process play. Each lesson varies in medium to expose tactile touch and expression, tools used to work on fine motor skills, and project size and scale to stimulate visual cues. Perfect for memories MAKE-ing and using both Your and your babie's right brain!

This is a fun focused class working together with Mom.

Begins February 19 and then every other Wednesday.
Morning session info: https://makepaducah.com/event/mommy-me-morning-session/

Perfect for memories MAKE-ing and using both Your and your babie's right brain!

This is a fun focused class working together with Mom.
